Based on the previous result from slides, I increase the value of \(\beta\) so that we have more reports. Then I slightly decrease the \(\mu_IR\) so that the peak wont come so quickly. In the end, I changed the parameters for report gerneraton so that there is no too much volatility.

6.2

Simulation of POMP model for following parameters.

Parameter \(\beta\) \(\mu_{IR}\) \(\rho\) \(k\) \(\eta\) \(N\) \(\mu_{EI}\)
Figure 1 28 0.3 0.55 500 0.03 38000 0.5
Figure 2 40 0.35 0.5 500 0.03 38000 0.9

Firstly, I starts with the parameters from previous question and setting the transition rate from exposed to infectious \(\mu_{EI}\) to be 0.5. The result is not good enough because the peak is low and coming too late. Whats more, there are too much noise after the peak. Therefore, I tuned the parameters of \(\mu_{EI},\mu_{IR},\rho\) to make it better.
